{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e807e3a3-0bab-40eb-ba02-58c9f567ba9e","content":"With Microsoft.Testing.Platform on .NET 8, the VSTest flags move to MTP equivalents after a `--` separator:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --collect-coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\nYou'll also need these NuGet packages in your test project:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump\" />\n```\n\n**Key mapping:**\n| VSTest | MTP |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--collect-coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n> **Note:** `--filter` stays before `--` (it's handled by `dotnet test` itself). With .NET 9+ SDK, the `--` separator is no longer needed as `dotnet test` has native MTP integration.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5af8684e-3969-4904-843d-09b6a625ea06","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) on .NET 8. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences between VSTest and MTP:\n- `--filter` → `--filter` (same)\n- `--logger trx` → `--report-trx` \n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--collect-coverage` with format option\n- `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`\n- `--blame-hang` → `--hangdump`\n- `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` → `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\n\n- On .NET 8, `dotnet test` doesn't have native MTP integration yet, so you'd need to either run the test executable directly or use `--` to pass arguments through to MTP.\n- With MTP, the flag mappings change: `--filter` works for basic filtering (or `--treenode-filter` for native MTP filtering), TRX reporting requires the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` package with `--report-trx`, and code coverage uses `--collect-coverage` with `--coverage-output-format cobertura`.\n- For crash and hang diagnostics, I'd use `--crashdump` and `--hangdump` with `--hangdump-timeout` respectively, each requiring their corresponding extension packages.\n- The command syntax differs between .NET 8 SDK (which routes through VSTest compatibility) and .NET 9+ SDK (which has native MTP support in `dotnet test`), affecting how arguments are passed and whether they go before or after the `--` separator. I need to identify the required NuGet packages for the Microsoft Testing Platform setup—specifically `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` for test result reporting, `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` for coverage collection, and the crash/hang dump extensions to support those diagnostic flags.","outputTokens":1466,"requestId":"0C03:2B0E8:22513B:284145:69F0057C"},"id":"645672b8-e9c6-4ab1-9152-f693e372979d","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:55:49.742Z","parentId":"831d919e-0867-4070-a7ea-2e94c75a1cac"}
